>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Greek Mythology — Legendary Terms That Score Big","description":"Greek mythology words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. SPHINX (18pts), PHOENIX (19pts), NYMPH (15pts), HYDRA (12pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-mythology-greek"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is PHOENIX a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! PHOENIX scores 19 points (P=3, H=4, O=1, E=1, N=1, I=1, X=8) as a 7-letter word. The X tile alone contributes 8 points. Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is SPHINX worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"SPHINX scores 18 points (S=1, P=3, H=4, I=1, N=1, X=8). The combination of H=4 and X=8 makes it a powerful 6-letter play."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play NYMPH in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! NYMPH scores 15 points (N=1, Y=4, M=3, P=3, H=4). It's notable for having no standard vowels — only Y acts as the vowel sound, making it useful for consonant-heavy racks."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Greek Mythology — Legendary Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Greek mythology gave us more than epic stories — it gave Scrabble players some of the highest-scoring words in the dictionary. PHOENIX, SPHINX, and NYMPH all pack premium tiles (X, H, PH) into memorable words that are easy to recall under pressure. These mythological terms are legitimate plays that can turn a game around.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">19 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PHOENIX (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SPHINX</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">NYMPH</p></div>
