      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Mythology Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">NYMPH is the vowel-free weapon:</span> With no A, E, I, O, or U — only Y as vowel — NYMPH (15pts) rescues consonant-flooded racks. Remember it when you're drowning in consonants.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SPHINX targets X placement:</span> The X in SPHINX (18pts) should land on a premium square whenever possible. Double Letter on X alone adds 8 more points.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">PHOENIX is a bingo dream:</span> At exactly 7 letters, PHOENIX (19+50=69pts) is one of the highest-scoring bingos possible without premium squares. Hold P, H, X and fish for the rest.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Greek mythology words are <span class="text-white font-medium">X and H specialists</span>. PHOENIX (X=8), SPHINX (X=8), NYMPH (H=4), and HYDRA (H=4) all leverage these premium tiles. Memorise this short list — when you draw X or H, mythology has your answer.</p>
      </div>
